      explanation: `## Evidence for Closure Timing

### Golden Period Studies
- Original animal data
- Human studies less definitive
- Contamination more important than time
- Well-irrigated wounds may close later

### Face Wound Data
- Lower infection rates
- Better blood supply
- Extended closure window safe
- Cosmetic benefit of closure

## Technique Comparison

### Tissue Adhesive vs Sutures
| Outcome | Adhesive | Sutures |
|---------|----------|---------|
| Cosmesis | Equivalent | Equivalent |
| Infection | Similar | Similar |
| Dehiscence | Slightly higher | Lower |
| Time | Faster | Slower |

### Staples vs Sutures (Scalp)
- Equivalent outcomes
- Faster application
- Cost effective
- Appropriate for most scalp wounds

## Advanced Closure Techniques

### Deep Dermal Sutures
- Reduce tension
- Better cosmesis
- Absorbable material
- Buried knots

### Mattress Sutures
- High tension wounds
- Wound eversion
- Horizontal or vertical

### Running Sutures
- Rapid closure
- Good for long wounds
- Less control per segment

## Complications

### Dehiscence
- Excessive tension
- Infection
- Early suture removal
- Technical error

### Infection
- Contamination
- Foreign body
- Inadequate irrigation
- Inappropriate closure

### Poor Cosmesis
- Wound edge inversion
- Unequal bites
- Excessive tension
- Delayed suture removal`,
